'''Wil Jhonems''' was the marketing manager for the [[Spotts TradeChip Company]] on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] in [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]].

He defended the controversial [[Jedi TradeChips]] line to [[HoloNet News/Legends|HoloNet News]], stating that the Jedi were better role-models for children during the turbulent times of the [[Separatist Crisis/Legends|Separatist Crisis]] than the professional athletes who appeared on most [[tradechip]]s. He also tried to explain away the inaccurate information on the tradechips, pointing out that Spotts did the best they could without access to the [[Jedi Archives/Legends|Jedi Archives]] library, and that corrections could be made in the next set.

